        {
          "md": "Weston: If you look carefully at the heads of Bugs Bunny, Petunia and Porky, you will occasionally see small black lines where drawings were pasted over Barks's originals. Barks said of the story: \"a few of the Porky or Petunia faces may have been reworked by the staff artists in the editorial room. All of the Bugs heads had to be redrawn, which pleased me very much. I am sure that if my Bugs had been acceptable, the office would have added that series to my work load.\" (letter, August 21, 1974)",
          "value": "Weston: If you look carefully at the heads of Bugs Bunny, Petunia and Porky, you will occasionally see small black lines where drawings were pasted over Barks's originals. Barks said of the story: \"a few of the Porky or Petunia faces may have been reworked by the staff artists in the editorial room. All of the Bugs heads had to be redrawn, which pleased me very much. I am sure that if my Bugs had been acceptable, the office would have added that series to my work load.\" (letter, August 21, 1974)",
